I was very lucky to be a part of Brian's R learning journey

00:35:01.684 --> 00:35:04.243
as an R mentor for him.

00:35:04.643 --> 00:35:07.363
By the way, I saw a question in the chat that said, is there a Hangout

00:35:07.363 --> 00:35:09.243
that's for Python? This is for everybody.

00:35:09.243 --> 00:35:12.964
We happen to be probably slightly overrepresented in R,

00:35:13.564 --> 00:35:17.603
but we have Python users, Excel users, SQL people, data engineers.

00:35:17.603 --> 00:35:19.883
We have all kinds here. Everybody is welcome.

00:35:19.883 --> 00:35:25.003
But Brian is the type of person who will go,

00:35:25.924 --> 00:35:28.204
hey, I have a question about this thing and this thing.

00:35:28.204 --> 00:35:28.924
And what about this?

00:35:28.924 --> 00:35:31.643
And and then he will go off and he'll do a bunch of stuff

00:35:31.643 --> 00:35:33.883
and then he'll come back and be like, look at all this stuff I did.

00:35:34.124 --> 00:35:35.803
What do you think about this?

00:35:35.803 --> 00:35:38.643
Where he like was really resourceful and kind of found out a bunch of stuff.

00:35:39.643 --> 00:35:40.603
That's what I look for.

00:35:40.603 --> 00:35:43.124
It's like, oh, somebody who's going to be really, really resourceful,

00:35:43.484 --> 00:35:47.443
go out on their own and solve things, come back and show me what they did

00:35:47.924 --> 00:35:50.083
with no ego attached to it.

00:35:51.603 --> 00:35:53.723
That's what I that's the person I want to work with.

00:35:54.443 --> 00:35:58.204
Yeah. And then I think also people who want to

00:35:58.603 --> 00:36:02.243
and this goes along with curiosity, but want to talk to other people, too,

00:36:02.723 --> 00:36:06.443
and go like figure out what their day to day is like

00:36:06.443 --> 00:36:09.523
and like what's behind that challenge or what's behind that question

00:36:09.523 --> 00:36:11.243
that they're asking, too.

00:36:11.243 --> 00:36:13.924
I think we hear that come up so much in the hangouts, too,

00:36:13.924 --> 00:36:16.243
about the importance of communication.

00:36:17.564 --> 00:36:22.083
Yes. I did not say Brian's last name out loud,

