And it says, how did you manage to put together such a positive

00:37:27.203 --> 00:37:28.803
and authentic community?

00:37:28.803 --> 00:37:33.284
Did you ever have issues with, for lack of a better word, toxic community members?

00:37:34.004 --> 00:37:36.243
Rachel, do you want to start with that first?

00:37:36.243 --> 00:37:37.083
You started the hangout.

00:37:37.083 --> 00:37:42.124
Or, yeah, I think it goes back to when you are intentionally building

00:37:42.124 --> 00:37:44.923
something small from the ground up.

00:37:46.404 --> 00:37:50.404
It's about making sure you have a diverse group

00:37:50.404 --> 00:37:53.643
from the beginning as well and inviting

00:37:54.363 --> 00:37:57.043
different people, different roles into the space.

00:37:57.444 --> 00:37:59.243
But I think

00:38:00.444 --> 00:38:04.684
sometimes you have to like take a step back and think about like,

00:38:05.564 --> 00:38:09.444
what do I need to say to make this space welcoming?

00:38:09.724 --> 00:38:15.964
And think about what if someone was joining for the first time every time?

00:38:16.604 --> 00:38:20.124
It can get easy for us to maybe think like,

00:38:20.124 --> 00:38:23.604
oh, people have been here before, so they know what to expect.

00:38:24.124 --> 00:38:27.724
But we're pretty intentional about at the beginning of every hangout

00:38:27.724 --> 00:38:29.844
explaining what it is.

00:38:29.844 --> 00:38:32.004
How do you ask questions?

00:38:32.004 --> 00:38:35.763
That this is a safe split, a safe space for everybody

00:38:35.763 --> 00:38:39.483
that you can ask questions anonymously if you want to.

00:38:40.483 --> 00:38:44.284
And I think that's really important for your own community events to like

00:38:44.284 --> 00:38:47.404
always let people know what they can expect.

00:38:48.604 --> 00:38:52.444
I would say like one of the like toxic things

00:38:52.444 --> 00:38:56.404
I noticed in the beginning when it first started is like

00:38:57.043 --> 00:39:00.884
there was almost this like battle of languages that would happen in the chat.

00:39:01.604 --> 00:39:07.523
